1. cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper deals with the problem of vehicle re-identification using attribute-guided feature learning, which is a subfield of computer vision. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The proposed Attribute-Guided Network (AGNet) is an end-to-end learning model that uses attribute features to learn global representation, which falls under the category of machine learning. 
3. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper deals with the analysis of urban surveillance videos, which is a multimedia application. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The use of attribute features to improve the performance of vehicle re-identification can be considered as an application of artificial intelligence. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security): Although not the primary focus of the paper, the problem of vehicle re-identification has implications for security and surveillance, which falls under the category of cryptography and security.
